5 Sec. 6c. (1) Beginning April 1, 2016 and each calendar quarter
6 thereafter through September 30, 2025, every person storing, using,
7 or consuming aviation fuel, the storage, use, or consumption of
8 which is subject to the tax imposed by this act when the tax was
9 not paid to a seller, and every seller collecting the tax from the
10 purchaser from sales of aviation fuel shall, on or before the last
11 day of the month in the month that immediately follows the end of a
12 calendar quarter, file an informational report with the department
13 on a form prescribed by the department showing all of the following
14 for the immediately preceding calendar quarter:
15 (a) The entire amount of taxable aviation fuel sold or
16 purchased by the person, as applicable.
17 (b) The amount of tax for which the person is liable from the
18 purchase or sale of aviation fuel.
19 (c) The number of taxable gallons of aviation fuel sold or
20 purchased by the person, as applicable, at each airport and the
21 gross proceeds from the sales or purchase of those gallons of
22 aviation fuel, as applicable.
23 (d) Any other information the department considers necessary
24 for the proper administration of this act.
25 (2) The report required under this section shall must not
26 include any remittance for tax and does not constitute a return or
27 otherwise alleviate the person's obligations under section 6.
28 (3) A person required to file the informational report under
29 this section that fails or refuses to file the informational report
