1 within the time and in the manner specified in this section shall
2 be is liable for a penalty of $10.00 per day for each day for each
3 separate failure or refusal up to, but not exceeding, a maximum
4 penalty of $500.00 for each separate violation. The department may
5 waive the penalty if the taxpayer demonstrates to the satisfaction
6 of the department that the failure to file was due to reasonable
7 cause.
8 (4) As used in this section, "aviation fuel" means fuel as
9 that term is defined in section 4 of the aeronautics code of the
10 state of Michigan, 1945 PA 327, MCL 259.4.
11 Sec. 21. (1) Except as otherwise provided in this section, all
12 money received and collected under this act must be deposited by
13 the department of treasury in the state treasury to the credit of
14 the general fund, to be disbursed only by appropriations by the
15 legislature.
16 (2) The collections from the use tax imposed at the additional
17 rate of 2% approved by the electors on March 15, 1994 must be
18 deposited in the state school aid fund.
19 (3) In addition to the money deposited in the state school aid
20 fund under subsection (2), from the money received and collected
21 under this act for the state share, an amount equal to the sum of
22 the following, as determined by the department, must be deposited
23 in the state school aid fund:
24 (a) All revenue lost under the state education tax act, 1993
25 PA 331, MCL 211.901 to 211.906, as a result of the exemption of
26 personal property under sections 9m, 9n, and 9o of the general
27 property tax act, 1893 PA 206, MCL 211.9m, 211.9n, and 211.9o.
28 (b) All revenue lost from basic school operating mills as a
29 result of the exemption of personal property under sections 9m, 9n,
